# Integration Layer

All external services live in `src/lib/integrations/` following the provider pattern.

## Architecture

```
types.ts          → Interfaces (VoiceSynthesisProvider, MemoryProvider, etc.)
config.ts         → Feature flags + lazy singleton registry
qwen-tts.ts       → TTS + voice cloning via Qwen3-TTS-Flash (DashScope)
mem9.ts           → Persistent cloud memory via mem9.ai
mem9-lifecycle.ts  → Fire-and-forget helpers (seed profile, store events, search)
fish-audio.ts     → Legacy Fish Audio provider (kept for reference, not imported)
```

## Adding a New Integration

1. Define the interface in `types.ts`
2. Implement in a dedicated file (e.g. `new-service.ts`)
3. Add feature flag + lazy loader in `config.ts`
4. Wire lifecycle events in the relevant API routes

## Optional pgvector mirror (`USE_PGVECTOR_MEMORY=1`)

- Dual-writes alongside mem9 from `mem9-lifecycle.ts`; search prefers pgvector hits when enabled
- Requires Postgres + `expert_memory_embeddings` (see admin migrate SQL); `OPENAI_API_KEY` for embeddings (else text fallback)

## mem9 (Persistent Memory)

- Free tier, no API key — space IDs are the only credential
- Each expert gets their own space (`Expert.mem9SpaceId`)
- Auto-provisioned on profile publish via `ensureExpertSpace()`
- Profile data seeded as initial memories (bio, domains, services, social links)
- Bookings and reviews stored as events
- AI match enriched with memory search results
- All mem9 calls are fire-and-forget (`.catch(() => {})`) — never block the request

## Voice Synthesis (Qwen3-TTS)

- Standard voices: `qwen3-tts-flash` with named voices (Ethan, Cherry, etc.)
- Cloned voices: `qwen3-tts-vc-2026-01-22` with voice ID from cloning
- Voice IDs stored in `Expert.fishAudioModelId` (legacy column name, stores Qwen voice IDs)
- Gender-based defaults: male → "Ethan", female → "Cherry"

## Voice Input (Qwen3-ASR)

- Server-side ASR via `POST /api/speech-to-text`
- Client records with `MediaRecorder`, sends audio blob to server
- `useVoiceInput` hook in `src/hooks/use-voice-input.ts`
